The aim of this document is to set up a template which will allow a user to input some data and then create a report based on the data that the user has inputted. It will eventually be downloaded through Shiny. To keep things simple, it will be easiest to start in HTML. Aims:
  1. A serparate page for each player which gives some summary statistics and graphs for each player.
  2. Similarity rating between players: this would be useful because it’s much easier to judge performance relative to something
  3. Some team statistics and statistics for groups of players, e.g. midfielders etc.
  4. One page of very high level feedback;for when the coach only wants an overview of what is going on. Which players have underperformed, which players are performing the best, some projections would be nice.
    Necessary steps to achieve this:
  1. Obtaining a full dataframe would be best. If the data comes in a specified format, the validation and error checking should be done before the data gets this far.
  2. Design an individual player page template which has been paramterised
  3. Fill in the template for each player
  4. Design a team template.
  5. Parameterise the template and check that it has been filled in correctly
  6. High level team statistics
